---

<div class="w-full flex flex-col justify-center items-center font-bold gap-10">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:pl-32">
        <div>
            <img src="" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="w-full bg-grisT p-8 flex flex-col gap-6 justify-center">
            <div>
                <img src="" alt="">
            </div>
            <div class="w-full md:pr-32 rounded-2xl">
                <p class="text-white text-base md:text-lg">
                    A continuous cleaning system that keeps the filter bags online at all times. A burst of compressed air is released through
                     a super sonic nozzle, creating an airwave that rapidly inflates the bag and dislodges the dust cake from its surface. The
                      detached particles fall into the hopper below, ensuring uninterrupted filtration and optimal bag performance.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full bg-bgBeige md:px-32 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 py-4">
        <div>
            <h1 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Triaso Supersonic Nozzle</h1><br>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-grisT">
                Our supersonic nozzles are 3D printed in-house using carbon alloy materials for exceptional resistance to impacts,
                 high temperatures, and vibrations. Ensuring highly efficient fine particle collection in the baghouse.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <img src="" alt="">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:px-32">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-grisT">
            The gas stream enters the baghouse’s inlet chamber after passing through the primary dust collector. 
            As it slows down, it flows beneath a protective barrier that shields the filter bags. Negative pressure from the clean air 
            plenum draws the gas upward through the bags. Fine particles collect on the outer surface of the bags, while the cleaned air passes 
            into the plenum and exits through the exhaust stack.
        </p>
        <img src="" alt="">
    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 md:pl-32 gap-6">
        <div class="w-full flex flex-col justify-start">
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">
                Self-contained and integrated dust control systems for efficient air filtration and particulate matter capture.
            </h2>
            <Separator/>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-grisT">
                Baghouses are crucial for controlling dust and maintaining air quality in industrial settings. They efficiently capture
                 particulate matter, ensuring compliance with environmental standards and creating a safer work environment. Ideal for industries 
                 like asphalt plants and aggregate processing, baghouses offer reliable, long-lasting performance.
            </p>
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl my-10">
                Elimination of sludge pits and their costly operation.
            </h2>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-grisPPP">
                Manufacturing highly protable self-contained, and integrated models, Triaso® baghouses operates at an air to cloth ratio as high as 8:1.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full flex flex-col gap-6">
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">
                Mechanism of baghouses available in pulse jet and reverse jet
            </h2>
            <div class="md:pr-32 bg-blueMain py-4 md:pl-4 text-grisSubP text-base md:text-lg md:rounded-l-2xl">
                <p>
                    <span class="text-whtie"> Pulse Jet: </span>A cleaning system that uses compressed air bursts to dislodge dust and debris from the filter bags,
                     maintaining continuous airflow.
                </p><br>
                <p>
                    <span class="text-whtie">Reverse Air: </span> A cleaning system that blows air in the opposite direction to remove dust from the filter bags, 
                    typically used in larger baghouses or high-dust applications.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:pr-32 bg-redBg py-4 md:pl-4 text-grisSubP text-base md:text-lg md:rounded-2xl">
                <h2 class="text-white text-xl md:text-2xl">
                    Different Types of Filter Bags and Their <br> Specific Applications:
                </h2>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6">
                    <li>Polyester</li>
                    <li>Nomex</li>
                    <li>Polyamide (P84)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex justify-start md:px-32">
        <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">Typical Venturi System</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 px-8 md:px-32">
        <div>
            <img src="" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="text-base md:text-lg text-grisT text-justify">
            <p>
                In venturi-based filtration systems, the airflow design introduces multiple inefficiencies that affect both dust collection and 
                system durability. The high-speed airflow exiting the venturi creates a low-pressure zone at the upper section of the filter bag,
                 pulling dust toward that area. This causes uneven accumulation and reduces filtration capacity. Over time, fine particles become
                 embedded deep within the fabric, making cleaning less effective.
            </p><br>
            <p>
                Another issue is the placement of the cleaning air pulse near the bag opening. This location limits its ability to draw in 
                additional air that could improve dust removal. Meanwhile, the narrow venturi forces filtered air to accelerate rapidly into 
                the plenum, creating upward airflow that resists the cleaning pulse. As a result, stronger air blasts are needed, increasing 
                energy use and putting mechanical stress on the bags—leading to faster wear and reduced lifespan.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex justify-end md:px-32">
        <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">Triaso High Ratio System</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 px-8 md:px-32">
        <div class="text-base md:text-lg text-grisT text-justify">
            <p>
                The new series baghouse improves dust removal by completely redesigning the airflow process. Instead of relying on a traditional
                 venturi system, it uses a supersonic converging-diverging nozzle to generate the cleaning air jet. This shift in design allows 
                 for the induction of more secondary air, enhancing the cleaning efficiency. The removal of the venturi also reduces the throat 
                 velocity at the bag’s inlet, preventing the negative pressure that typically leads to dust buildup at the top of the filter bag.
            </p><br>
            <p>
                By fully utlization of the bag mouth, the cleaning air jet expands evenly, minimizing the likelihood of dust cake blowout. Leading 
                to a more uniform bag inflation, resulting in a more effective cleaning cycle and reduced wear on the fabric. 
                <span class="text-black">As a result, the Triaso
                 Model only requires half the filter area compared to traditional venturi systems</span>, enabling Triaso to offer high performance in a more 
                 compact form.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <img src="" alt="">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex flex-col justify-start md:px-32">
        <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">Triaso Exhaust System</h1><br>
        <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Gas extractor with curved blade fan, more efficient and quieter.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 md:px-32">
        <div>
            <img src="" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="w-full rounded-2xl p-4 bg-white text-justify text-base md:text-lg text-grisT">
            <p>
                The Triaso Extractor is designed to effectively manage airflow and ensure optimal gas filtration in the asphalt plant. 
                With its curved blade fan, the extractor pulls gases through the system while maintaining efficient air circulation. By 
                keeping external contaminants out, it helps maintain internal pressure at the necessary levels for consistent operation.
            </p><br>
            <p>
                It operates using centrifugal force to separate dust from exhaust gases. As the gas enters, it spirals along the inner walls, 
                where heavier particles are pushed outward. Approximately 70% of the total dust load falls to the bottom for collection, reducing 
                the burden on the baghouse filters, improving efficiency, and extending their service life.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:px-32 px-8 text-base md:text-lg">
        <p>
            The finer dust particles are directed into the baghouse through a strategically placed high side inlet. This ensures horizontal 
            and downward airflow, preventing fine dust from being re-entrained into the system. A knockout chamber decelerates airflow,
             allowing more material to drop into the hopper, while internal baffles ensure even air distribution and protect the bags from abrasion.
        </p><br>
        <p>
            This design optimizes air quality, enhances filtration efficiency, and minimizes maintenance requirements, 
            ensuring a more effective and reliable operation.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:px-32 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-20">
        <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Durable Construction</h2><br>
            <p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg text-justify">
                Our bin units are engineered with wear-resistant materials that excel in handling abrasive and heavy loads. 
                This robust construction ensures the system remains reliable even under the harshest working conditions. By minimizing wear and tear,
                 the design significantly reduces maintenance requirements and extends the system’s lifespan, providing a dependable solution for 
                 long-term operations.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Customizable Settings</h2><br>
            <p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg text-justify">
                The dosing system offers unparalleled flexibility to accommodate the unique demands of each project. With options for both manual 
                and automatic adjustment, the system ensures precise control over material flow. This versatility allows seamless handling of a wide 
                range of materials, from fine aggregates to bulkier substances, optimizing efficiency and ensuring smooth integration into any 
                operational setup.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex justify-start px-32">
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">Baghouses Fines Hoppers</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full text-base md:text-lg px-32">
        <div class="w-full bg-white text-justify p-4 rounded-2xl text-grisT">
            <p>
                The finer dust particles are directed into the baghouse through a strategically placed high side inlet. This ensures horizontal and downward 
                airflow, preventing fine dust from being re-entrained into the system. A knockout chamber decelerates airflow, allowing more material to drop
                 into the hopper, while internal baffles ensure even air distribution and protect the bags from abrasion.
            </p><br>
            <p>
                This design optimizes air quality,<span class="text-black"> enhances filtration efficiency, and minimizes maintenance requirements</span>,
                 ensuring a more effective and reliable operation.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:pr-32 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-20 items-end">
        <div class="w-full">
            <div class="w-full md:ml-32 h-0.5 bg-redBg mb-2">
            </div>
            <div class="w-full md:mr-32 h-0.5 bg-blueMain">
            </div>
            <div>
                <img src="" alt="">
            </div>
        </div>
        <Card>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-grisT">
                Positioned directly below the filter system, these hoppers allow for controlled collection of fines, 
                which can then be temporarily stored, discharged, or reintegrated into the asphalt mix—depending on the plant’s configuration.
                 They play a crucial role in maintaining clean air emissions and supporting the environmental performance of the asphalt plant.
            </p>
        </Card>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex justify-end md:px-32 px-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Fines Return System</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:px-32 text-justify text-grisT">
        <p class="text-grisT text-base md:text-lg">
            Once the baghouse collects fine particles in the hoppers, a screw conveyor transfers the fines back into the drum mixer. 
            This return is carefully timed and positioned—right where the liquid asphalt is injected—ensuring the fines are immediately coated 
            and bonded into the mix.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:px-32 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-20">
        <div class="w-full">
            <Card>
                <p class="text-grisT text-base md:text-lg">
                    By reintegrating the fines at this specific point, the system prevents them from becoming airborne again, 
                    reduces material loss, and improves the quality and durability of the asphalt. This efficient recovery not only enhances 
                    environmental performance but also maximizes resource use for a more cost-effective operation.
                </p>
            </Card>
            <Separator/>
        </div>
        <div>
            <img src="" alt="">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex justify-start md:px-32">
        <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Features</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:px-32">
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-grisT text-base md:text-lg">
            <li>Modular and fast-to-install design.</li>
            <li>Top-access snapband bags for easy maintenance.</li>
            <li>Reinforced housings and galvanized wire cages with built-in super sonic nozzles.</li>
            <li>Wide bag spacing for optimal airflow and minimal wear.</li>
            <li>Custom ducting and pre-installed air systems.</li>
            <li>Integrated screw conveyor for fines handling.</li>
            <li>Available in configurations up to 90,000 ACFM.</li>
            <li>Tool-free access to service components.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <GallerySlider slides={tanksSlides} visibleThumbs={4}/>
</div>